{"word":"H8334 - שָׁרַת - shârath - shaw-rath' - Minister","slug":"H8334","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שָׁרַת</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shârath"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shaw-rath'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Minister"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E8;&#x05EA; - sha&#x0302;rath</b> - <i>shaw-rath'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>attend</i> as a menial or worshipper; figuratively to <i>contribute</i> to: - minister (unto), (do) serve (-ant, -ice, -itor), wait on."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8335\">H8335</a>, <a href=\"#/H8336\">H8336</a>"}]}